Amazon has launched its new Fire HD 8 tablet. The device offers an 8-inch HD display (1,280 x 800) and is available in two models – each in one of four colours: Amazon said the tablets also support microSD cards up to 400GB for additional storage. Powering the tablet is 1.3GHz quad-core processor, 1.5GB of RAM, and an “all-day” battery. A front-facing 720p camera and a rear-facing 2MP camera are also included, along with dual-band Wi-Fi support. “Amazon-exclusive” features with the Fire tablet are Alexa, ASAP, For You, X-Ray, Second Screen, Amazon FreeTime, Family Library, Blue Shade, On Deck, and Prime Video downloads, added the company. The tablet launches on 4 October 2018.